  "original_title": "\"\u0db8\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0db8 \u0db0\u0db1\u0dba, \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dda \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba\"",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"My greatest wealth, treasure was my library\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Making a special statement this evening (11), Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe said that his library and his only house, which is his greatest wealth, was destroyed due to the fire that was set on his private house at Fifth Lane, Colombo 7 on the night of the 9th.",
        "He further emphasized that more than 2500 very valuable books and very old works of art in his library were waiting to be donated to schools, universities and other educational institutions and now almost all of them have been destroyed.",
        "He said that those who have Hitlerite thoughts can behave like this.",
        "Also, he stated that the current situation is not a crisis that can be solved very quickly in view of the weak economic situation in the country, and he came forward to take this responsibility knowing the suffering of the people."
      ],
